<subSubSection id="4EB76509E7665577FF2B0E27FE7AB2A1" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="336" pageId="1" pageNumber="335" type="description">
<paragraph id="06123682E7665574FF2B0E27FDB6B239" blockId="1.[151,1436,152,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7665574FF2B0E27FEA5B27F" bold="true" box="[199,338,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">Description.</emphasis>
Male, length of forewing 
<quantity id="C1559B67E7665574FD6D0E27FCF1B27F" box="[641,774,290,313]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="335" unit="mm" value="4.4" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="4.1">4.1–4.7 mm</quantity>
(n = 
<number id="B06524A5E7665574FCA10E27FCABB27F" box="[845,860,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="335" value="3.0">3</number>
). General color uniformly brown, in alcohol. Head relatively elongate, flattened; postocular parietal sclerite large (slightly extending below eye); anterior setal wart divided. Wing venation typical for the subgenus.
</paragraph>
<caption id="52D2660AE7665574FF7B08BCFA6CB4B5" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="335" targetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="06123682E7665574FF7B08BCFA6CB4B5" blockId="1.[151,1436,1977,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7665574FF7B08BCFEE2B488" bold="true" box="[151,277,1977,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C1AD4D01E7665574FEF108BFFDADB489" box="[285,602,1978,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Chimarra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machadoi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Otarrha">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7665574FEF108BFFE76B489" box="[285,385,1978,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">Chimarra</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7665574FE7E08BFFE12B489" box="[402,485,1978,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">Otarrha</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7665574FE1A08BFFDADB489" box="[502,602,1978,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">machadoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2FEA57EBE7665574FD8E08BFFD42B489" box="[610,693,1978,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7665574FD8E08BFFD58B489" bold="true" box="[610,687,1978,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="335">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="06123682E7655577FF2B0F9DFAA0B282" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7655577FF2B0F9DFE9EB3E9" box="[199,361,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FE920F9DFE4EB3E9" box="[382,441,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Fig. 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FE430F9DFE4EB3E9" box="[431,441,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
): Tergum VIII with short paired dorsal processes from posterior margin, acute apically, narrowly separated basally (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FE3E0FBFFDE0B397" box="[466,535,186,209]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Figs 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FDE10FBFFDE0B397" box="[525,535,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, E). Abdominal segment IX with anteroventral margin expanded, invaginated mesally; posteroventral process narrow, elongate, rounded apically, gradually tapering from base to apex (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FAD90FD8FA83B3B2" box="[1333,1396,221,244]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Fig. 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FA860FD8FA83B3B2" box="[1386,1396,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A); anterodorsal margin deeply concave (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FDC90E05FD96B251" box="[549,609,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Fig. 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FDBA0E05FD96B251" box="[598,609,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B); posterolateral margin sinuous (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FC3F0E05FBF8B251" box="[979,1039,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Fig. 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FBE90E05FBF8B251" box="[1029,1039,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Tergum X divided in mid-section into two simple elongate apically rounded mesal lobes, contiguous basally, each with apical sensilla; lateral lobes short, acute, tapering at apex (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FE4E0E40FE15B21A" box="[418,482,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Fig. 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FE3B0E40FE15B21A" box="[471,482,325,348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Preanal appendages short, oval, earlike, flattened (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FBD00E40FB89B21A" box="[1084,1150,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Figs 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FB990E40FB89B21A" box="[1141,1150,325,348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B). Inferior appendage simple; in lateral view strongly curved upward almost in a right angle, tapering to apex; in dorsal and ventral view short, with mesal rounded expansion, strongly incurved apically (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FCFC0E8FFCB8B2E7" box="[784,847,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Figs 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FCAA0E8FFCB8B2E7" box="[838,847,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D). Phallic apparatus with tubular phallotheca, with no sclerotized apical projections; phallotremal sclerite T-shaped; endotheca with 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FC190EA8FBF5B282" box="[1013,1026,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="6.0">6</number>
sclerotized spines (
<figureCitation id="9E962A07E7655577FB380EA8FAE4B282" box="[1236,1299,429,452]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,441,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[277,1315,438,1959]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chimarra (Otarrha) machadoi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. lateral view; B. dorsal view; C. inferior appendage, ventral view; D. inferior appendage, dorsal view; E. tergum VIII, dorsal view; F. phallus, ventral view; G. phallus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257576/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
Figs 
<number id="B06524A5E7655577FAE60EA8FAE4B282" box="[1290,1299,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F–G).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06123682E7655577FF2B0ED5FE7AB2A1" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,695]" box="[199,397,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7655577FF2B0ED5FED4B2A1" bold="true" box="[199,291,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">Female:</emphasis>
Uknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4EB76509E7655577FF2B0EF7FB10B109" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="06123682E7655577FF2B0EF7FB10B109" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7655577FF2B0EF7FEB0B14F" bold="true" box="[199,327,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is described in honor of Dr. Angelo B. M. Machado, a brilliant medical doctor, entomologist and expert on Odonata, science communicator and writer of fictional books with educational and scientific approach for children. His dedicated and multidisciplinary work is an inspiration to Brazilian scientists.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4EB76509E7655577FF2B0D5FFDE1B1F1" pageId="2" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="06123682E7655577FF2B0D5FFDE1B1F1" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="34D9EA90E7655577FF2B0D5FFECFB137" bold="true" box="[199,312,602,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="336">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species was found in rapidly flowing, cool water streams with some deep pools along their course. Cerrado riparian forest of semi-deciduous trees was observed along margins. The streams have primarily rocky bottom, with leaves and sand in lentic areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
